{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011XaWotM6xiV1TQwwoabXSP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Secrets created. Now I need to update the StatefulSet to:\n1. Remove `--insecure` flag\n2. Add `--certs-dir=/cockroach/cockroach-certs`\n3. Mount the node cert secret as a volume at `/cockroach/cockroach-certs`\n4. Update the liveness/readiness probes to use HTTPS instead of HTTP (since the HTTP admin UI will also be TLS)\n5. Also mount the client certs on the pods so that the `cockroach sql` command can use them\n6. The health check endpoints work over HTTPS in secure mode, so I need to set the probe scheme to HTTPS\n\n.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the data migration aspect. Since the cluster is currently running in insecure mode with existing data, switching to secure mode isn't as simple as just updating the configuration. CockroachDB requires all nodes to be stopped, the configuration updated, and then all nodes restarted together. With a Kubernetes StatefulSet rolling update, there's a timing issue—once node-0 switches to secure mode, it can't communicate with nodes still in insecure mode. The solution is to update the StatefulSet and perform a coordinated restart across all nodes simultaneously. and 2 in insecure mode, which breaks quorum. I need a coordinated restart where all nodes transition simultaneously. I can either scale down to zero and back up, or patch the StatefulSet with settings that allow parallel pod updates. Since the StatefulSet already has parallel pod management enabled, I'll patch it with the secure configuration and let all pods restart together.\n\nUpdating the StatefulSet with certificate volumes and changing from insecure mode to using the certs directory...\n\nFor the SQL verification test, I need both the node certificates and the client root certificates mounted at `/cockroach/cockroach-certs` so the command can access `ca.crt`, `client.root.crt`, and `client.root.key`.\n\nI could use a projected volume to merge both secrets together, or alternatively use an init container to copy them, or consolidate everything into a single secret.\n\nSince both secrets contain `ca.crt`, I need to be careful—projected volumes will use the last one when there's a name collision, but since they should be identical anyway, that works fine.\n\nActually, the simpler approach is to create one combined secret with all the necessary files: `ca.crt`, `node.crt`, `node.key`, `client.root.crt`, and `client.root.key`. Then I just mount this single secret at `/cockroach/cockroach-certs` and everything's in one place.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":758,"cache_read_input_tokens":33881,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":758},"output_tokens":38,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ee286e43-8864-4637-8fac-0885289ebc0c","uuid":"434a115b-c5a4-421e-9a88-d44aca71f6bd","request_id":"req_011CcMu1cX2CxWDypyM9i7Ta"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011XaWotM6xiV1TQwwoabXSP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll create a combined cert secret (node + client) and patch the StatefulSet to use TLS."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":758,"cache_read_input_tokens":33881,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":758},"output_tokens":38,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ee286e43-8864-4637-8fac-0885289ebc0c","uuid":"d634010d-5fd0-42f6-b992-e69acbd61290","request_id":"req_011CcMu1cX2CxWDypyM9i7Ta"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_011XaWotM6xiV1TQwwoabXSP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018fAYKuFdVecTHEHcTS1NrU","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"# Create a single combined secret with all certs (node + client.root) for the pods\nCA_CRT=$(kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- cat /tmp/certs/ca.crt)\nNODE_CRT=$(kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- cat /tmp/certs/node.crt)\nNODE_KEY=$(kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- cat /tmp/certs/node.key)\nCLIENT_CRT=$(kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- cat /tmp/certs/client.root.crt)\nCLIENT_KEY=$(kubectl -n cockroachdb exec crdb-cluster-0 -- cat /tmp/certs/client.root.key)\n\nkubectl -n cockroachdb create secret generic crdb-certs \\\n  --from-literal=ca.crt=\"$CA_CRT\" \\\n  --from-literal=node.crt=\"$NODE_CRT\" \\\n  --from-literal=node.key=\"$NODE_KEY\" \\\n  --from-literal=client.root.crt=\"$CLIENT_CRT\" \\\n  --from-literal=client.root.key=\"$CLIENT_KEY\" \\\n  --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\n\necho \"Combined secret created\"\nkubectl -n cockroachdb get secret crdb-certs -o jsonpath='{.data}' | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(list(d.keys()))\"","description":"Create combined cert secret with all needed files"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":758,"cache_read_input_tokens":33881,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":758},"output_tokens":38,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ee286e43-8864-4637-8fac-0885289ebc0c","uuid":"262eb97c-e2bf-49d5-8e07-d8cb4e91d6b4","request_id":"req_011CcMu1cX2CxWDypyM9i7Ta"}
